 visit here to see upcoming events hosted by aec and campus partners! sign up for upcoming workshops hosted by aec! spring 2023 faculty process for administering accommodated exams spring 2023 student process for accommodated exams [pdf] aec continues to take steps to ensure that all communication sent to students is held secured and confidential – therefore all email communication sent to students from the aec will be sent to students' sjsu-issued email address. to assist students in this transition, aec has created a tutorial [pdf] on how to forward messages from student sjsu-issued email accounts to a preferred email account (e.g. gmail, yahoo, hotmail, etc.). if you have a student in your class with mobility needs, and the student must use an elevator to access your classroom, the aec is providing you with information to assist you and the student for after-hours support in the event the elevator is non-functioning. for assistance after 5:00 pm call the university police department (upd). upd will call the facilities developments& operations (fd&o) on-call manager. the on-call manager will contact kone, elevator maintenance service under contract. the contract stipulates kone has 1 hour to arrive on campus for a call back. office emails staff directory administration building (adm) room 110 accessible education center san josé state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0168 mon: 9 am - 5 pm tues: 9 am - 5 pm wed: 10 am - 5 pm thurs: 9 am - 4 pm fri: 9 am - 4 pm 